caption: The most delicious Massaman curry!  Very inviting and accomodating owner...hard to find service like this these days.  Please support them.
Amazed with the carry-out. Food was still delicious by the time I walked home. Owners are nice and pour their heart into their restaurant.
The owner is so sweet and incredible, always gives extra food and the food is awesome.

The best Thai restaurant in Chicago. Serving Chicago's Boystown, Lakeview, & Wrigleyville since 1983. They've lasted decades for good reason. The owner, Sue, & her sister still run this place like they did in their 20s. My go to PS Bangkok order is a Chive Dumpling appetizer with a Gwey Teo Noodle soup.The Khao Soy is exquisite as well as the Pad See Ew with crunchy noodle option for the main entree. For dessert their Mango Sticky Rice is to die for, when in season. Make sure to order a Singha or Chang Thai beer to cool the burn.

This was our favorite Thai food restaurant.  We hadn't been there for a while,  so we decided to order pick up for dinner.  What a disappointment.  The Pad Thai tasted like they used reheated, old stale noodles as well as old oil.  It tasted nothing like what we remembered.  It vaguely resembled Pad Thai at all. The Pad see ewe was bad as well tasting a few days old.  I don't write reviews at all, but I had to write this one because of how bad it tasted.
This have been my fav Thai place in all of Chicago since the 1990.  Always reasonable, amazing food and a wonderful darling owner!  Please continue to support this amazing family owned place!!!
The food was fantastic and the owners are wonderful! Will definitely be ordering from here again!

If you have somewhere to be after your meal, allow extra time. That being said, the food here is AMAZING and vegan friendly and the woman I spoke with was so kind and gracious. I will be coming back here as often as I can! Such a great experience.
the best restaurant in chicago. the owner is so sweet. the service is amazing and the food is delicious. green curry was amazing!!! highly recommended and will surely come back again
I love the open and friendly atmosphere. I always enjoy my food and recommended choices by the staff.
If you're in for savory Thai noodles, Thai curry, or any Thai themed foods this is the spot. Spicyness is done decently.

My boss recommended this place and my goodness this place is Michelin star good. Speaking of they were recognized by Michelin as a top tier restaurant in the wrigleyville neighborhood. Definitely a treat to come visit
Good food, and the owner is super polite and friendly!
The khao soi was incredible. I asked the owner for a surprise and that's what she gave me.

Food was not good, meat was low quality, really overpriced, and really small volume (half a chicken on the menu turned out to be half a chicken breast at best). would recommend literally any other place.
Very nice place, the lady was very nice to me and my girlfriend the whole night. The food was pretty good. My favorite food that I ate tonight though here was a chicken satay appetizer.

Food is not really good. Tom Yum was extremely sour. Rica & vegetable was so-so. Seafood no salt -no sauce. Service is extremely slow. And it was just 3 of us and 1 more table. Not recommend to other!!!!
username: Life is too short to drink bad wine

caption: Outstanding food, very authentic and delicious.  Everything was cooked from scratch. Wonderful conversation a nice atmosphere. Great experience...thank you
The owner is the nicest lady. I got the pad Thai and it was amazing, some of the best I’ve had. I highly recommend and the atmosphere is nice
Food is amazing and the server is so sweet.... I’ve been to 20 other Thai places and this one is the best! Highly recommended
Not the place I will ever go back
Quiet restaurant that makes really fantastic and flavorful food at a very reasonable price considering the area. It's run by a very amicable lady and their service makes it a pleasure to dine there!

Great food, fantastic service, for a moderate price. Food: Appetizers - The Knomjeeb (Shumai) has fresh, flavorful shrimp in it, and Spicy Eggrolls are delicious, and Huge! To Drink - can't go wrong with a sweet and refreshing Thai Iced Tea, perfect for keeping cool through any spicy bites! Entrees - I love Pad Thai, it's my go-to at every Thai restaurant, so I've seen it all. P.S. Bangkok's Pad Thai was great because of the quality ingredients, large portion, and best of all, they provide the spice on the side so you can add as much as you want, perfect for Anyone, from spice-addicts to people who want to enjoy Pad Thai but aren't big fans of spice. I loved it. The Stir-fried Seafood Curry is on a whole other level. The perfect combination if seafood mixed with a mildly spicy curry, basil and pepper, with a side of perfectly steamed, sticky white rice. This was served in a beautiful flower-designed arrangment, in a portion large enough for two to split. Save room for dessert! The fresh fruits and sweet, milky rice are absolutely worth it! Service: Phenomenal. The server took such great care of us! They were friendly, helpful, attentive, and made us feel right at home. I love them! The food came in short amounts of time, and the ambience of the restaurant is so comfortable yet elegant, I was stunned. Price: Very affordable. The quality of this food is on par with the fanciest restaurants you can find, but the pricing is easily half of what you'd pay elsewhere. The service is perfect, and leaves nothing wanting. Basically, the best bang for your buck you can hope to find.

The food is really good. I had the best beef salade ever, the sauce was amazing. My son likes a lot the Tom Kha soup as starter as well chicken satay. Definitely try the green curry!! The service is really friendly, a little bit slow but we were not in hurry.

Best Thai restaurant in Chicago. Don’t go to any other Thai restaurant in Wrigleyville—this place is by far the most authentic Thai. No other place comes close. Go here if you want delicious food and a friendly staff!
I grew up in Thailand. If you’re looking for authentic Thai, this is the place.
love
A nice local spot with a nice change from all the burger and pizza joints in the area. They offer a good selection of meals and appetizers, beers, and service was very friendly.
Amazing.

Food was delicious. I can’t get over how friendly they were! Felt like I was eating at my grandparents. The owners were so sweet to us and our son. We all left with smiles.  Will definitely be going back!

The women running the restaurant were very nice, but this is some of the worst Thai food I've ever had. My green curry had a strange smell as soon as I opened it and the chicken had a weird look. After one bite, of watery curry I regretted my order. I tried to eat it but ended up throwing the entire dish away. The fried tofu appetizer had a very strange consistency and tasted like it had been fried in really old oil. That was also quickly thrown away. The quality of the meat, taste, and freshness were all really questionable.  Try another place if you're craving Thai.
Had an amazing and delicious first time here. Great ambience and super friendly owner. Loved the view of the sunset over the L. Going back already tonight!
High quality. Unique items and fairly priced.
Green curry was LEGIT.
Absolutely amazing!!!! One of the best Thai places I have ever been. All meals made from scratch. If you want thai this is the place to go.

When was the last time you ate dinner at your grandma's house? She cooked for you, brought it to the table, and wanted to do everything she could to make sure you enjoyed her work. This experience comes pretty damn close. The food was authentic and outstanding. The presentation mattered to the staff, and the server was attentive and offered suggestions for us along the way. The atmosphere was classic, and really made the evening feel like we were not in Chicago (in a good way!). I noticed the server pause to ensure we enjoyed the first bite before walking too far away, and our reaction was genuine to the great flavors. She seemed to get a lot of joy from the work she does. Please go and enjoy their passion with them.
Amazing authentic Thai food, love it!

Usually when you go to an empty restuarant, its a bad sign. This place is real authentic with great tasting food. The owner is a very kind older woman and I would recommend going with her recommendation. I got the pad Thai and its some of the best I've ever had.
Don't be scared off if it's empty, it's really good!

Had such a delicious meal here. Super authentic Thai food. It is run by two sisters, and food is homemade so it’s not the best place to go if you’re in a big hurry. Some of the best Thai food I’ve ever had. Try the tarot root fritters—so yummy. Of the 3 dishes we ordered, all were fantastic with the Pad See Won being my favorite. Don’t be deterred by an empty restaurant, we almost were but were so glad we stayed!

If you love authentic Thai, definitely try this place!  Quality/flavor of their food is outstanding, and it is beautifully presented.  We were waited on one of the owners, who was extremely gracious, offering us a lovely item off the menu because they weren't very busy at the moment (I can't fathom why not).  Art prints, sculpture, and other decor added to the Thai ambiance.  Thoroughly enjoyable!
I wish more people could know how amazing this place is, the owner and her sister are the kindest individuals I have ever known. Words can't tell how amazing the food was
This place is great!! The spicy pepper egg rolls especially. Ms Sue is a sweetheart and takes really good care of her customers. Definitely give this place a try!
Best Thai. No joke about the spice levels.
The food was delicious!!!! You can tell everything was made from scratch. Definitely will be going back.
Food & service was excellent & reasonably priced.
Food and service were great. Careful how spicey you ask for. I am from out of town and come to Chicago once a year and P. S. Bangkok will be a go to when in town.
I’ve come here many times, and these many times I’ve had decent service. Thanks
Best Thai food I have ever tried! Everyone is so nice and the best thing is that the food has a lot of taste! Panang curry is a must try and also the corn cakes and the chicken saytay!
Hands down best authentic Thai in Chicago 💜
Good food but took over an hour to get it.

We came here because my partner remembered this was her first taste of Thai food when her class came on a field trip 20 years ago. The food is delicious! I was feeling adventurous so I told the owner what I like and don't like and asked her to surprise me. I highly suggest you try that. She really knew how to pick out something I wouldn't have tried for myself but that would really make me happy. She has a whole menu and program for large groups; teachers, you can call ahead and bring a group up to a hundred if you're going to a local museum. Otherwise, it doesn't seem like it's often crowded, which is a real shame for such good food and great service!
The dish I had was below average, greasy and sour. Not impressed. Don’t recommend.
Tremendous, unapologetically original Thai dishes. Enthusiastic owner clearly cares about the food she serves
Best Thai food period

If you are looking for high quality authentic tasting Thai food, this is the best in Chicago. I've tried ten other places in the city and this is the best one. Be careful choosing the spiciness level. The spice scale is 1 to 5 and a 2 here is like a 5 everywhere else. I would recommend getting a one the first time you go and then guage what level you want when you go back to try something else. And I promise the quality will merit a second visit.
Wonderful Pad Thai
Very cute place, good food and kind service.. The fresh spring rolls were kinda disappointing but the rest was great.

We where just there today on 8/13/17 Sunday after Market Days in Chicago and the food was very good. Excellent service and the owner was very helpful towards the menu and any questions we might have. Where thinking of going back and try other food in the menu. Recommend to other people. 👍😋
Outstanding tasty thaï food, great family hosts
Love this place! Friendly staff and Great service. Authentic Thai food, my favorite is the Lotus Blossom Curry if you enjoy seafood
The best most authentic tasting Thai food I've found around here.  Great little place, not too expensive and the food was fantastic!  Made me feel like I was in Thailand again.

The owner Su was absolutely hospitable towards my family. She reminded me of my grandma. The space is small but charming; plenty of traditional Thai decor. Most importantly, the food was delicious! But beware: the food is super spicy by default, so be sure to ask for there to be very little or no spice if heat isn't your thing. I would definitely recommend eating here if you're craving Thai cuisine.
Got a 1.5 on the heat scale and cryed while eating it. Amazing.
Great food
I ordered a spicy red curry with fish and it was excellent. My girlfriend said her Pad Thai was not that great. The restaurant looks a bit formal, but has nice authentic furniture and decor.
I was presented with Pad Thai consisting of noodles, vinegar and peanuts! OK + sprouts. Thank was it! Not worth your visit

Excellent green curry and Thom Ka Gai. The only issue we encountered on our visit was that the Larb we ordered came with too much fish sauce, but our server offered to bring us a new order and strike it from our tab. A very pleasant experience, overall.
Best Thai food in Lakeview

This is some of the best Thai food I've ever had! The hostess was wonderful and warm and when I looked into the kitchen window, there was an elderly woman walking around back there. After I got home it dawned on me, "That's why this food is so good, this is grandma's home cooking, Thai food style!"
The owner is very nice and she can make your food very spicy!

Our go-to Thai for three years! Unsurpassed quality of meat and veggies. Highly recommend the chicken in spinach noodles and the Chinese broccoli in garlic sauce! The owner Sue is always there and she cares about her food and her customers.

Love the food, come here every time I'm craving any thai food. The menu is enormous and fantastic. I live  the area and come here often.  If you want spicy food this is your jam,  they can turn it up to 11 here!

I've eaten here more times than I can count, Its a big favorite among my friends in the area. If you want real Thai food that is completely brutal in the heat department, this is the place to go. All the chili paste is made from scratch, not the store bought weak stuff I find at other Thai restaurants that are around in the area. The main Server is an awesome person, She is always ecstatic to see my group of friends, knows us all by name and makes sure we go home with extra food. She also likes to make fun of me when I get red faced and sweating profusely from the heat content. Seriously, if you like spicy savory food this is the place to go!

If I could give less than one star I would. I wish I'd never had a craving for Thai food and never went to that place that night. The first clue should have been that nobody was there except us, yet the restaurants around us were full. They acted like they didn't want us there and the lady was the rudest person I'd ever met. I asked for a lemon in my water but she acted like I wanted a kidney. The service was painfully slow and when the food finally did come it was cold and tasted like garbage. I was afraid I was going to get food poisoning from it and didn't eat it. When we pointed that the meat was undercooked and nasty she still ,are us pay for it and then didn't give me back my change. At that point I just wanted to get out of there. Seriously do not go to this place. I don't understand the good reviews. It blows my mind that anyone could give this place a good review. I wish someone had warned me and I could have went somewhere else and not wasted my money . I could have gone have to Panda Express and been way happier.
Worst place I've ever eaten. Service slow and we were only ones there. Food cold and pork undercooked. Made them aware and they still charged for it. Worst food and service in Chicago

AUGUST 7, 2016 | My daughter's crispy noodle Pad Thai was just a plate full of crushed peanuts and nearly burnt noodles. It tasted AWFUL! It taste like a metal skillet. She took 2 bites and when we wanted to send it back, she wanted us to pay for the plate. She also gave my friend a pork dish instead of chicken and tried to convinced her to keep it. We left and ended up paying for the dish. YOU SHOULD ONLY HAVE TO PAY FOR WHAT YOU ATE! In addition my shrimp was under cooked. We went to Clark Street Dog down the street and she enjoyed that!

We thought the food was fantastic; the decorum was stylish, and the prices were relatively inexpensive for Thai food.  The restaurant seems to  have been here for a while, but there weren't many patrons for a Friday night. They also did not honor their "15% OFF on Cubs home games" advertisement. We would definitely  go back!

this place is AWFUL. the WORST place ive ever been to hands down. first of all i waited an hour (they're 1 block away) even after she told me 10 minutes . When it got here, the rice resembled/tasted of unflavored oatmeal, and the pad thai was just as inedible. Those two (nasty) dishes plus 2 bottled waters was $28. for low grade sub par might as well of been cat food. actually would have preferred fancy feast that was past date. please save your self the effort and never go here you will regret it. i wish i could give this place no stars but unfortunately google only allows for 1 star.
Very nice. It was very quite when I went. The server made a recommendation that I really enjoyed.

The best Thai food in the city. This Zagat rated restaurant is fantastic. Be wary of the spice scale. Sue (the owner) has a scale 1 through 5 and won't even eat a 3. That said, the food can be as mild as you want it, and I recommend this place before any other Asian food in the city.

Food: 2 Decor: 3 Service: 3  I came here for lunch with a friend who works at McKinsey.  1. A10. Beef Paradise, 7 ~Pretty good, although I wish it could have been a bit hotter.  2.  E54. Love Me Tender Duck, 11 ~Disappointing. Duck still had some bone and could have been crispier, and the lemon sauce absolutely ruined the dish. My crispy noodles ended up soggy, so I didn't eat much of it.  Service was okay, although my friend got force-fed the last piece of beef and a lecture on Asians fighting over the bill.  Lunch specials not valid on Sundays, even though it says so on the menu.
Excelent service. Amazing beef tenderloin. And the red snapper in peanut sauce was the best I had. This place is a must try for any Thai fan.
Such a nice lady, quick service, and great food!!! Literally tamarind #48 is amazing !
hands down the best chicken panang you will ever find.
They have the best khow soy I've ever had in my life 😍
Had pho and it was really good, along with excellent customer service.  My favorite

Overpriced and not that good compared to most of the other Thai places in Chicago that I've tried. They charge you extra to add meat into your dish, and that's on top of the high prices they already have on the menu. They also charged me like $3-4 extra to change a vegetable in my entree

Two of my friends from the suburbs SWEAR by this place and come here whenever they come up to the city, but I wasn't a fan. I got the Pad Thai and it was super bland. I feel like that's a hard dish to mess up, but I was not impressed.

I went to P.S. Bangkok for lunch to taste for an upcoming luncheon. The Owner Sue you have to meet she is so nice (:) she makes you feel so at home. The food is delicious Entrees and Appetizers. Don't forget to order dessert  "Cantaloup Cake or Banana Pudding"  with Coconut ice cream SO GOOD. Any thing you order the taste is so fresh and different. You have to put this on your list to visit. Loved every dish, atmosphere and hospitality (Sue).

Waited over an hour for our food while other patrons were walking out. Staff never made an attempt to communicate any issues. After paying was literally told, "please don't be mad."  Wow, just... Wow...
Great food! Always timely delivery or pick-up. The owner is so kind and friendly.
This is the best thai food I have come across!!! Great quality, always fresh and inexpensive!! The woman that owns it is very friendly. It's never that crowded but don't let that fool you!!
Great and authentic food, but service was sluggish
The food was cooked in sugar. Every dish tasted the same due to the sweetness.
Pad Thai and Pad-See-Ewe are amazing, well best I ever had. Enough food for 2 with most takeout orders.
the food was reasonable, but not good enough to compensate for the extremely poor service. i was disappointed at best.
